711361f-a.title: Manhattan: 13th Street - 10th Avenue
711361f-a.text:
At the intersection of Tenth (right), and Eleventh (left) Aves., at
Wgnst 13th Street, and looking northward. The 3-story house at the apex, is
known as the Strand Hotel, and bears Nos. 2-4 Eleventh Ave., as well as No.
500 West 14th Street. Beyond that,is seen, the National Biscuit Co. plant
at Wwst 15th extending to 16th Streets, and facing on both Aves. Two bridges.
connect the main plant with a new annex, through which pass the elevated
tracks of the New York Central R.R.
Marah 31, 1937.
P. L. Sperr.
NO REPRODUCTIONS.
